title: Sense and Sensibility (Version 3)
creator: Jane Austen
description: LibriVox recording of Sense and Sensibility (Version 3), by Jane Austen. Read by Elizabeth Klett. Sense and Sensibility, Jane Austen's first published novel, focuses on the lives and loves of two sisters, Elinor and Marianne Dashwood. The sensible Elinor and the sensitive Marianne both fall for men whose affections are otherwise engaged. The novel includes a wonderful cast of colorful supporting characters, as well as Austen's trademark dry wit and ironic narration. (Summary by Elizabeth Klett) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; love; romance; Jane Austen; Elinor Dashwood; Marianne Dashwood; John Willoughby; Edward Ferrars; Colonel Brandon;
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: Elizabeth, I thoroughly enjoyed your narration of this awesome Jane Austen's work. Thank you for the clarity, eloquence and competence which clearly pours our of this audio work.

Wow, Elizabeth Klett's reading really brings Austen's biting critique and humor to light.  Listening, I hear so much of the irony and sarcasm that I miss reading silently to myself.

Another great job Elizabeth!  Thanks for your dedication!
